            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>soft cheese</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p><p>Once the shallot has browned, add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> to the pan, cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until the Tenderstem is softened and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1666189406299-x200.jpg",
